    • getOtherPartyPayment

      public List<Payment> getOtherPartyPayment()
      Gets the value of the otherPartyPayment property.

      This accessor method returns a reference to the live list, not a snapshot. Therefore any modification you make to the returned list will be present inside the Jakarta XML Binding object. This is why there is not a set method for the otherPartyPayment property.

      For example, to add a new item, do as follows: 

          getOtherPartyPayment().add(newItem);
